
Overview of noun beacon

The noun beacon has 3 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (1) beacon, beacon fire -- (a fire (usually on a hill or tower) that can be seen from a distance)
2. radio beacon, beacon -- (a radio station that broadcasts a directional signal for navigational purposes)
3. beacon, lighthouse, beacon light, pharos -- (a tower with a light that gives warning of shoals to passing ships)

